And he said...

921
01:13:28,433 --> 01:13:31,811
if I didn't pay him
that he would hand it over to the police.

922
01:13:37,233 --> 01:13:39,569
All right. Let's go see Whiting.

923
01:13:40,194 --> 01:13:42,582
I don't know where he is.
I swear I don't know.

924
01:13:42,686 --> 01:13:46,899
Listen, lady, any day now
some hotshot detective at Homicide...

925
01:13:47,003 --> 01:13:50,694
is going to tumble on the fact
that this is more than a simple robbery.

926
01:13:50,799 --> 01:13:53,739
When they do,
they're going to come looking for Whiting.

927
01:13:53,843 --> 01:13:56,096
If the cops tag him for killing his wife...

928
01:13:56,200 --> 01:14:00,214
they'll nail you as an accessory
just as sure as I'm sitting here.

929
01:14:04,052 --> 01:14:07,586
There's this place over at Fountain
and La Cienega where we used to meet.

930
01:14:07,691 --> 01:14:10,308
All right. Let's go.

931
01:14:12,018 --> 01:14:15,261
Things haven't
really been going so great lately.

932
01:14:15,365 --> 01:14:17,659
Not as well as they might have gone...

933
01:14:17,763 --> 01:14:22,695
but I don't think that's reason enough
for you to give up everything.

934
01:14:24,197 --> 01:14:26,814
Charlotte, there's one thing I want to say.

935
01:14:26,918 --> 01:14:30,964
You know this town doesn't change.
They just push the names around.

936
01:14:31,068 --> 01:14:34,874
If you want to change managers,
far be it for me to stand in your way.

937
01:14:35,458 --> 01:14:38,002
I'm just not that type, so go ahead.

938
01:14:41,673 --> 01:14:45,551
I'm telling you, Mr. Wells,
Walter wouldn't be here without me.

939
01:14:46,260 --> 01:14:47,595
We'll see.

940
01:14:51,432 --> 01:14:53,643
No. Walter.

941
01:14:55,645 --> 01:14:56,854
Walter?

942
01:15:06,656 --> 01:15:09,325
God. Oh, my God!

943
01:15:16,457 --> 01:15:19,335
Ronny did this. Ronny killed him.

944
01:15:21,004 --> 01:15:23,923
Hi, this is Margo Sperling. Is Ira Wells in?

945
01:15:24,716 --> 01:15:26,676
Oh, God. No.

946
01:15:27,593 --> 01:15:31,796
If he calls, would you tell him, please,
to call me? It's very important.

947
01:15:31,900 --> 01:15:34,600
Margo. Okay, thanks a lot.

948
01:15:52,577 --> 01:15:55,621
- C.S. Hatter Productions.
<i>- Charles, it's Margo.</i>

949
01:15:56,748 --> 01:15:59,115
<i>Do you know where Ira is?</i>
<i>I've got to talk to him.</i>

950
01:15:59,219 --> 01:16:01,826
How the hell would I know?
What's the matter?

951
01:16:01,930 --> 01:16:03,828
<i>Something funny has happened.</i>

952
01:16:03,932 --> 01:16:06,559
<i>I was going to feed Winston tonight.</i>

953
01:16:06,664 --> 01:16:11,377
<i>I've had a lot of trouble getting him back</i>
<i>on schedule since the kidnapping...</i>

954
01:16:11,481 --> 01:16:15,141
<i>and I looked down</i>
<i>and I found this gun laying on the floor.</i>

955
01:16:15,308 --> 01:16:17,174
- No shit.
<i>- I'm pretty sure it's real...</i>

956
01:16:17,279 --> 01:16:21,564
<i>- and I want to find Ira...</i>
- Margo, don't worry. I'll handle it.

957
01:16:29,072 --> 01:16:32,825
I was here this afternoon.
My husband must have followed me.

958
01:16:38,873 --> 01:16:41,250
Mr. Wells, I'm scared.

959
01:16:42,085 --> 01:16:44,472
If my husband can do something like this
to Walter...

960
01:16:44,577 --> 01:16:48,091
he'll do the same thing to me. He'll kill me.

961
01:16:49,676 --> 01:16:51,552
You've got to help me.

962
01:16:53,221 --> 01:16:56,015
It's raining everywhere these days, lady.

963
01:16:56,516 --> 01:16:59,477
That gun of yours,
the one you gave Whiting...

964
01:16:59,852 --> 01:17:03,523
- it was a.32, right?
- I think we should call the police.

965
01:17:10,029 --> 01:17:11,864
Why don't you do that?

966
01:17:12,532 --> 01:17:15,357
I'd like to be around
when you try and explain to the cops...

967
01:17:15,462 --> 01:17:18,454
that Whiting's wife
was murdered in this dump.

968
01:17:18,579 --> 01:17:21,635
Mrs. Whiting caught you
and her husband here one night.

969
01:17:21,739 --> 01:17:25,336
There was a fight.
When it was all over, she ends up dead.

970
01:17:27,505 --> 01:17:31,968
Mr. Wells, some of the things
I told you before were untruths.

971
01:17:34,762 --> 01:17:36,347
Still not there?

972
01:17:36,764 --> 01:17:41,060
Tell him that I called again...
Wait, I think this is him. Thanks a lot.

973
01:17:44,897 --> 01:17:46,774
- Ira...
- Hiya, doll.

974
01:17:47,316 --> 01:17:50,153
Margo Sperling. Ron Birdwell, Jeff Lamar.

975
01:17:50,445 --> 01:17:53,270
I'm tied up right now.
I'm working on something.

976
01:17:53,375 --> 01:17:55,940
Would you mind waiting in...
Don't you push me.

977
01:17:56,044 --> 01:17:57,087
Okay.

978
01:17:57,379 --> 01:18:00,945
I'd like to invite you in,
but I've got work that I have to finish...

979
01:18:01,049 --> 01:18:04,219
so please don't sit down.
What do they think they're doing?

980
01:18:04,323 --> 01:18:07,670
Listen, remember that gun
that we were talking about?

981
01:18:08,046 --> 01:18:10,882
This guy Birdwell, he's willing to buy it.

982
01:18:13,217 --> 01:18:16,095
- What about Ira?
- Let me tell you something.

983
01:18:17,096 --> 01:18:21,340
Ira Wells was a broken-down old bum
who was never any good to start with.

984
01:18:21,444 --> 01:18:23,968
That schmuck blew every chance he had.

985
01:18:24,072 --> 01:18:26,241
And he'll blow this one, too, if I let him.

986
01:18:26,345 --> 01:18:28,013
We'll give him a couple of thou...

987
01:18:28,118 --> 01:18:31,944
let him go to the track
and act like a big shot. You know.

988
01:18:33,279 --> 01:18:34,583
Get them out of here.

989
01:18:34,687 --> 01:18:37,022
How the hell long
are you gonna stay in there?

990
01:18:37,127 --> 01:18:40,484
- Just a minute, pal.
- I mean it, get them out of here...

991
01:18:40,589 --> 01:18:42,789
- and you get out, too.
- Easy, now.

992
01:18:43,164 --> 01:18:46,031
Hold on. Listen. I'm running into a little...

993
01:18:46,136 --> 01:18:48,367
I'm through shitting around with you,
you putzola.

994
01:18:48,471 --> 01:18:51,172
I want you to give me the gun.

995
01:18:51,339 --> 01:18:55,927
Mr. Birdwell, I'm the one that has the gun.
I mean, it's in my possession.

996
01:18:56,636 --> 01:18:59,972
Charles told me
what you are offering and I'm...

997
01:19:00,556 --> 01:19:01,599
Wait!

998
01:19:05,520 --> 01:19:08,898
Hit her, for God's sake.
She's got the goddamn gun.

999
01:19:09,315 --> 01:19:11,943
- He has a point, Lamar.
- Wait a second.

1000
01:19:13,820 --> 01:19:17,990
If you lay a hand on me,
you're gonna pay for it in your next life.

1001
01:19:18,866 --> 01:19:21,369
Violence has never solved anything.

1002
01:19:21,994 --> 01:19:25,790
If you come one step closer,
I'm gonna break this right in your face.

1003
01:19:27,917 --> 01:19:29,252
Answer it.

1004
01:20:07,582 --> 01:20:09,375
Hello, doll. Ira.

1005
01:20:10,501 --> 01:20:12,378
<i>I'm at Whiting's place.</i>

1006
01:20:12,754 --> 01:20:15,923
<i>He's dead.</i>
<i>I've got this whole thing figured out.</i>

1007
01:20:16,299 --> 01:20:17,800
<i>- Ira...</i>
- Doll...

1008
01:20:18,301 --> 01:20:21,846
in case you're interested,
I know who killed Harry Regan.

1009
01:20:23,139 --> 01:20:24,182
It was Birdwell.

1010
01:20:24,515 --> 01:20:27,153
<i>Stay put, okay?</i>
<i>I'm on my way over to your place.</i>

1011
01:20:27,258 --> 01:20:28,770
Don't hang up...

1012
01:20:35,568 --> 01:20:36,611
Lamar...

1013
01:20:37,737 --> 01:20:41,699
how would you like a new Coupe DeVille,
color of your choice?

1014
01:20:46,746 --> 01:20:49,957
Mr. Wells, I cannot tell you
how good it feels...

1015
01:20:50,500 --> 01:20:53,221
to have finally opened up
and told the truth...

1016
01:20:53,325 --> 01:20:56,130
to have opened up
the dark side of my soul.

1017
01:20:56,339 --> 01:20:58,716
It's like stepping into the sunlight.

1018
01:21:09,560 --> 01:21:11,062
I'm all right.

1019
01:21:19,445 --> 01:21:21,771
Listen, he's an old guy. He's not even well.

1020
01:21:21,875 --> 01:21:24,210
He needs an operation,
one on his stomach.

1021
01:21:24,315 --> 01:21:26,953
I know we could talk this over
and work something out.

1022
01:21:27,620 --> 01:21:29,789
There's no reason to get him.

1023
01:21:30,623 --> 01:21:33,251
Mr. Birdwell, let me give you the gun.

1024
01:21:34,335 --> 01:21:36,129
Why don't I do that?

1025
01:21:36,379 --> 01:21:38,725
I don't know why
I didn't give it to you before.

1026
01:21:38,829 --> 01:21:42,124
I know how much you want it,
and I don't even care about the gun.

1027
01:21:42,228 --> 01:21:43,928
I'll do that, okay?

1028
01:21:46,931 --> 01:21:48,808
I'm going to stand up.

1029
01:21:51,310 --> 01:21:53,104
See? I'm standing up.

1030
01:21:53,688 --> 01:21:56,399
I'm just going to walk across the room.

1031
01:21:56,733 --> 01:21:59,444
Here I am. I'm walking across the room.

1032
01:22:00,820 --> 01:22:03,948
I'll open this drawer. See me opening it?

1033
01:22:04,866 --> 01:22:06,065
Just take it and go.

1034
01:22:06,169 --> 01:22:09,495
What about me? What about yours truly?
We had a deal.

1035
01:22:09,787 --> 01:22:12,133
"Twelve bills for the gun."
That's a direct quote.

1036
01:22:12,238 --> 01:22:16,210
You know, that old guy isn't so dumb.
He's right about Harry Regan.

1037
01:22:17,337 --> 01:22:18,838
I killed him.

1038
01:23:07,595 --> 01:23:09,681
- Ronny.
- You okay?

1039
01:23:10,348 --> 01:23:13,893
Darling, you must think
I'm such a terrible person.

1040
01:23:16,270 --> 01:23:17,313
Ira!

1041
01:23:21,984 --> 01:23:24,779
Do something. I told you he was sick.

1042
01:23:30,368 --> 01:23:32,495
You don't look so good, pop.

1043
01:23:37,583 --> 01:23:39,825
Ronny, you ever been to Florida?

1044
01:23:39,930 --> 01:23:43,016
They got these old turtles that crawl up
on the beach at night.

1045
01:23:43,120 --> 01:23:47,719
As a kid, I'd sneak up with a two-by-four
and flip them over on their backs.

1046
01:23:48,011 --> 01:23:49,595
They looked just like that.

1047
01:23:53,057 --> 01:23:55,560
A doctor. I want...

1048
01:23:56,269 --> 01:23:59,022
- What did you say, old man?
- I want a...

1049
01:24:02,608 --> 01:24:05,069
You wanna know something, punk?

1050
01:24:05,528 --> 01:24:08,698
You were born dumb,
and you're going to die dumb.

1051
01:24:12,744 --> 01:24:14,120
Now get up.

1052
01:24:15,246 --> 01:24:16,456
Get up!

1053
01:24:18,374 --> 01:24:19,625
Hurry up!

1054
01:24:23,296 --> 01:24:25,423
Park it over in that chair.

1055
01:24:31,262 --> 01:24:35,808
All right, sit down.
Keep your hands nice and quiet.

1056
01:24:37,727 --> 01:24:39,645
And your mouth shut up.

1057
01:24:43,191 --> 01:24:46,444
- Are you all right?
- Never been better.

1058
01:24:49,238 --> 01:24:52,909
Pretty nice. Pretty slick.

1059
01:24:54,285 --> 01:24:57,830
You knew if I fell for it,
they'd fall for it, right?

1060
01:24:58,706 --> 01:25:00,322
Of course I didn't fall for it.

1061
01:25:00,427 --> 01:25:03,638
You son of a bitch,
don't you even do that to me again.

1062
01:25:03,742 --> 01:25:07,507
What if I had fallen for it?
I could have had a heart attack.

1063
01:25:08,341 --> 01:25:11,146
Here's someone I really care about,
drop dead at my feet.

1064
01:25:11,250 --> 01:25:13,846
How am I supposed to feel about that?

1065
01:25:13,971 --> 01:25:17,089
Mentally deranged, that's how.
Probably for the...

1066
01:25:17,193 --> 01:25:19,487
Doll, you're still alive, aren't you?

1067
01:25:19,592 --> 01:25:23,189
That's another thing. Don't call me doll.
I don't like it.

1068
01:25:24,399 --> 01:25:27,860
- Pop, she's a real loony bird.
- You're not?

1069
01:25:30,279 --> 01:25:33,533
You don't mind if I sit down, do you?
I've had a tough day.

1070
01:25:39,205 --> 01:25:42,875
Kid, just hear me out
before you do anything crazy.

1071
01:25:43,376 --> 01:25:46,577
We've got this guy between
a rock and a hard place, see?

1072
01:25:46,681 --> 01:25:49,841
We're in a position
to make an A-number-one deal.

1073
01:25:50,925 --> 01:25:53,250
Nice to see a man who loves his wife.

1074
01:25:53,355 --> 01:25:55,753
Get used to something.
She doesn't love you back.

1075
01:25:55,857 --> 01:25:57,421
- Ronny, do something...
- Be quiet.

1076
01:25:57,525 --> 01:26:01,217
Laura kills Mrs. Whiting
at that love nest over on Fountain Avenue.

1077
01:26:01,321 --> 01:26:04,564
She calls Brian Hemphill
and gets him to clean up her mess.

1078
01:26:04,939 --> 01:26:07,765
Escobar and Brian move the body
back to Whiting's house...

1079
01:26:07,869 --> 01:26:11,529
and fake the stamp caper
to throw the cops off the track.

1080
01:26:11,779 --> 01:26:15,533
That's water over the dam.
Let's cut to the chase.

1081
01:26:16,159 --> 01:26:20,413
Escobar's got the gun Laura used
on Mrs. Whiting and blackmails her.

1082
01:26:20,830 --> 01:26:22,488
Somewhere along the way...

1083
01:26:22,592 --> 01:26:25,345
Birdwell realizes
if he can get a hold of that gun...

1084
01:26:25,449 --> 01:26:28,682
Laura will have to stick to him like glue
for the rest of her life.

1085
01:26:28,786 --> 01:26:31,883
Why are you putting my wife
under this pressure?

1086
01:26:32,050 --> 01:26:34,886
He and this joker go looking for Escobar.

1087
01:26:35,094 --> 01:26:38,796
They catch up with him at that palace
he had in Santa Monica...

1088
01:26:38,900 --> 01:26:40,631
put the arm on him...

1089
01:26:40,735 --> 01:26:42,758
but Lamar gets carried away and kills him.

1090
01:26:42,862 --> 01:26:44,270
I can see...

1091
01:26:45,813 --> 01:26:47,857
this is going to cost me.

1092
01:26:48,775 --> 01:26:53,404
By now Whiting's starting to get nervous.
He's in this mess way over his head.

1093
01:26:54,113 --> 01:26:56,084
He decides to go to the cops.

1094
01:26:56,188 --> 01:26:58,649
Laura couldn't afford that,
so she had to kill him.

1095
01:26:58,753 --> 01:26:59,859
That's a lie.

1096
01:26:59,963 --> 01:27:03,404
That's when you came to me,
hoping I'd play the sap for you.

1097
01:27:03,508 --> 01:27:06,584
- He's lying.
- No, that's exactly what happened.

1098
01:27:06,751 --> 01:27:08,659
You figure I'll want to talk to Whiting.

1099
01:27:08,763 --> 01:27:13,038
You take me there, I'll sniff around,
and think your husband killed him.

1100
01:27:13,143 --> 01:27:17,001
- You don't believe him, do you?
- I'm not saying you're right...

1101
01:27:17,105 --> 01:27:18,888
but what's the price?

1102
01:27:19,472 --> 01:27:23,685
I've been in this business 31 years,
give or take a couple of months.

1103
01:27:23,810 --> 01:27:26,479
I've always played it on the up and up.

1104
01:27:26,896 --> 01:27:30,149
- Call the cops.
- Hold it!

1105
01:27:31,192 --> 01:27:34,362
Put that thing down.
You haven't got the ass to swing it.

1106
01:27:35,363 --> 01:27:38,189
All my life I've been a loser,
from the day I was born.

1107
01:27:38,293 --> 01:27:40,493
What makes you any different now?

1108
01:27:40,618 --> 01:27:43,089
What makes you think
Birdwell's gonna sit still...

1109
01:27:43,194 --> 01:27:45,863
for some chiseler like you
to take that kind of dough off?

1110
01:27:45,967 --> 01:27:49,700
I'll make him, that's why.
Because I've got him by the short hairs.

1111
01:27:49,804 --> 01:27:52,703
Yeah, you'll make him,
just like Harry Regan made him.

1112
01:27:52,807 --> 01:27:55,435
Harry goes to Birdwell,
tries to deal himself in...

1113
01:27:55,539 --> 01:27:57,166
but Birdwell can't gamble on...

1114
01:27:57,270 --> 01:27:59,585
some two-bit chiseler
gumming up the works...

1115
01:27:59,689 --> 01:28:02,181
so they meet someplace for a payoff.

1116
01:28:02,682 --> 01:28:05,977
Birdwell unloads a.45 point-blank
into his stomach.

1117
01:28:17,697 --> 01:28:19,657
You dumb son of a bitch.

1118
01:28:21,034 --> 01:28:23,870
- Didn't I tell you you'd blow it?
- Mr. Wells.

1119
01:28:23,995 --> 01:28:25,788
Sit down and shut up.

1120
01:28:32,587 --> 01:28:34,005
Six figures.

1121
01:28:35,381 --> 01:28:37,842
He was going to pay us six figures.

1122
01:28:38,301 --> 01:28:43,097
Police emergency?
It's 3626 Franklin. Apartment 405.

1123
01:28:43,681 --> 01:28:46,267
We have a dying man here. Step on it.

1124
01:28:53,399 --> 01:28:55,360
Jesus Christ.

1125
01:28:56,069 --> 01:28:59,572
How did I ever get mixed up with you
in the first place?

1126
01:29:00,073 --> 01:29:03,076
You're right, Charlie. I'll never learn.

1127
01:29:07,580 --> 01:29:10,458
- I think maybe I better sit down now.
- Yeah.

1128
01:29:11,292 --> 01:29:12,627
All right.

1129
01:29:13,586 --> 01:29:15,797
- I think I'll sit down.
- Okay.

1130
01:29:25,098 --> 01:29:27,725
- You believe in reincarnation?
- I don't know.

1131
01:29:28,935 --> 01:29:31,104
Never thought much about it.

1132
01:29:32,105 --> 01:29:36,275
I hate to think of Charles
just floating around in the eternal void.

1133
01:29:36,484 --> 01:29:40,029
I like to think
he's gonna drop around again sometime...

1134
01:29:40,154 --> 01:29:42,615
even if he was pretty non-evolved.

1135
01:29:43,616 --> 01:29:44,659
You know what I mean?

1136
01:29:46,703 --> 01:29:50,331
Charlie did the best he knew how.
That's for sure.

1137
01:29:55,003 --> 01:29:56,671
Where you headed?

1138
01:29:57,005 --> 01:29:59,288
I was going to take this
number 10 to Highland...

1139
01:29:59,392 --> 01:30:00,664
then transfer to number four.

1140
01:30:00,769 --> 01:30:03,876
That should let me off a couple of blocks
from my house.

1141
01:30:03,980 --> 01:30:06,514
- What about you?
- I don't know.

1142
01:30:08,141 --> 01:30:10,560
Mrs. Schmidt asked me to move out.

1143
01:30:15,815 --> 01:30:18,985
That place next door to you,
is that still empty?

1144
01:30:20,862 --> 01:30:23,781
I don't know, I don't think I could take it.

1145
01:30:23,990 --> 01:30:26,419
You just never say anything,
for God's sake.

1146
01:30:26,524 --> 01:30:29,401
It's not fair. I've to keep up
